<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-74-0909 </DOCNO><TEXT>At the Mining Automation Center KOMAG and the Central Mining Institutethe TWO-1.5EH equipment was developed for setting LP-8 to LP-10 supportsmade of V36 and V44 sections. The operating principle of the TWO-1.5EHmanipulator is explained. The manipulator is suspended from a monorailand is operated using a hand-held push-button control box. The electricalequipment is encased in a fireproof casing and can be used in gas endangeredspaces with the c degree of gas hazards. The equipment has until nowonly been produced as a prototype. Development work has begun on thedesign of a similar piece of equipment with pneumatic drive and controland with a platform for 2-zone heading i.e. with support setting in theupper zone and loading in the lower zone. 3 refs.</TEXT></DOC>